  "texts": [
    "Remarkably, the model predictions provide a coherent framework for interpreting the measured dielectron spectra across a wide energy range and invariant mass regions.",
    "In the low-mass region, the predominant hadronic radiation is primarily attributed to the in-medium broadening, stemming from its interactions with the hadronic medium, particularly baryons.",
    "Notably, this model also yields a consistent description of the invariant mass spectrum of dimuon pairs measured by the NA60 experiment at the SPS [257].",
    "The observed in-medium broadening serves as a compelling indicator of the partial restoration of chiral symmetry within the hot QCD medium [258].",
    "However, in the intermediate-mass region, contribution from QGP radiation is anticipated although current measurements still lack precision in this regime."
